<item>
            <title>[SPARK-15826] PipedRDD to allow configurable char encoding</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15826</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Encountered an issue wherein the code works in some cluster but fails on another one for the same input. After debugging realised that PipedRDD is picking default char encoding from the JVM which may be different across different platforms. Making it use UTF-8 encoding just like `ScriptTransformation` does.&lt;/p&gt;

